law, can argue that it's okay to wipe out 500 of them in an air-raid shelter
because it was "deliberately" placed next to a legitimate military target,
and not see that Moffett Field, in Sunnyvale, is a legitimate military
target "deliberately" placed in the middle of thousands of civilians.)
<p>
Am I cynical? No, I don't think so. I think I'm realistic.
